<main>
    <section id="introduction" class="section">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>The Conflict Resolution Toolkit provides essential resources, strategies, and case studies for mediators and peacekeepers working in conflict zones. The goal is to support professionals in navigating complex social, political, and cultural challenges in order to foster peace and cooperation among conflicting parties.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="resources" class="section resources">
        <h2>Key Resources</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Training Workshops</strong> – Ongoing workshops designed for mediators to enhance their conflict resolution skills in real-world scenarios.</li>
            <li><strong>Conflict Resolution Framework</strong> – A proven framework for understanding and resolving conflicts through dialogue and negotiation.</li>
            <li><strong>Online Mediation Platforms</strong> – Digital tools for remote mediation that facilitate communication between parties in different locations.</li>
            <li><strong>Peacebuilding Literature</strong> – Access to a range of books, articles, and journals on the theory and practice of conflict resolution.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Resources</strong> – Access to international laws, treaties, and agreements that govern conflict resolution processes.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="strategies" class="section strategies">
        <h2>Effective Conflict Resolution Strategies</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Interest-Based Negotiation</strong> – Focus on the interests of both parties rather than their positions, allowing for creative solutions that satisfy both sides.</li>
            <li><strong>Active Listening</strong> – Actively listen to all parties involved, ensuring they feel heard and understood, which helps reduce tensions.</li>
            <li><strong>Building Trust</strong> – Establishing trust through consistent, transparent actions and communication is essential for long-term peace.</li>
            <li><strong>Neutral Facilitation</strong> – As a mediator, maintaining neutrality is crucial to ensuring that both sides feel the process is fair.</li>
            <li><strong>Conflict Mapping</strong> – Visualizing the key players, issues, and dynamics in a conflict to better understand its complexity and find effective interventions.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="case-studies" class="section">
        <h2>Case Studies</h2>
        <div class="testimonial">
            <h3>Case Study 1: Resolving Political Tensions in Country X</h3>
            <p>This case study focuses on how a mediation team used interest-based negotiation and active listening to defuse political tensions between two opposing factions in Country X. By focusing on mutual interests, the mediators helped both sides reach a historic peace agreement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="testimonial">
            <h3>Case Study 2: Conflict Resolution in Refugee Camps</h3>
            <p>In refugee camps, resources are often scarce, leading to disputes. This case study highlights how trust-building and neutral facilitation helped resolve a violent conflict between two ethnic groups within the camp, preventing further violence.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

